  "description": [
    "Davis Says Germany Cannot Be Defeated By Bombing Alone Asserts Decisive Victory Must Be Won by Ground Forces Following a threeweek tour of the European war theater Elmer Davis director of the Office of War Information is convinced that Germany cannot be beaten by air raids alone but must be defeated decisively on the ground before the European war will end Mr Davis told a press conference yesterday there was little doubt that largescale air attacks had seriously Injured Nazi production and morale He pointed out however that a large number of German Army di visions were still intact and ex pressed the conviction this land army must be beaten decisively This defeat he added may be in flicted by the Russians in the east or combined British and American forces somewhere on the continent Asked if he believed there would be a second front soon Mr Davis said he expected a third front to be opened though he did not specify where or when The Allies have a pretty good second front already operating in the Mediter ranean he added I dont think Germany can be beaten from the inside entirely said Mr Davis commenting on the effect on"
  ],
